  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-02 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels for this synthetic accepted package. One validation result — the most extensively narrated — is missing its structured prov:wasGeneratedBy link, introducing a broken-provenance weakness (W-EP-02). A reviewer may assume the detailed prose narrative substitutes for the structured activity reference.",
