      "name": "Absolute hemolysis index validation against five bench operating conditions — detailed multi-protocol assessment",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/synth/data/hemolysis-bench-measurements-5op",
      "description": "Hemolysis index predictions were obtained by post-processing converged CFD velocity and shear-stress fields through the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model. Simulations were executed on a 14.2 million cell polyhedral mesh using the k-omega SST turbulence closure at five operating points (4 L/min at 3000 RPM; 4 L/min at 4000 RPM; 5.5 L/min at 3500 RPM; 6 L/min at 2500 RPM; 6 L/min at 4000 RPM). Bench hemolysis measurements were conducted in triplicate using the modified hemolysis index (MHI) protocol per ASTM F1841. CFD predictions fell within ±18% of measured MHI values at four of five operating points; the fifth point (6 L/min, 4000 RPM) showed a 23% over-prediction attributed to cavitation-induced shear not captured by the continuum model. Monte Carlo propagation of inlet boundary condition uncertainty (±5% flow, ±2% speed) yielded 95th-percentile prediction intervals that encompassed all bench measurements. The assessment team reviewed raw simulation logs, mesh quality reports, and turbulence residual convergence histories prior to signing off on this result. All artefacts are archived in the project data repository under accession VAD-CFD-2025-HI."
    },
